OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774436770
OL,3,CTaxpayer support: The cavalry is
OL,4,Ccoming but not for everyone
OL,6,FITV News' Economics Editor Joel Hills
OL,7,Freports on what the chancellor can do
OL,8,Fto lessen the economic impact of the
OL,9,FIran war
OL,11,FThe sums are mind-blowing. Almost
OL,12,Fimpossible to grasp.
OL,14,FThe government spent #169 billion
OL,15,Fsupporting households and businesses
OL,16,Fduring the pandemic - on furlough,
OL,17,Fgrants for the self-employed, tax
OL,18,Frelief and loans for businesses.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31002
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774436770
OL,3,CTaxpayer support: The cavalry is
OL,4,Ccoming but not for everyone
OL,6,FIt then spent a further #62 billion
OL,7,Fwhen oil and gas prices surged after
OL,8,FRussia invaded Ukraine four years ago.
OL,10,FMuch of this money was borrowed. Add
OL,11,Fin higher interest rates and the
OL,12,Flegacy of such emergency help, the
OL,13,Fgovernment is now spending an extra
OL,14,F#67 billion every year just on debt
OL,15,Finterest.
OL,17,FThat is roughly the same as the entire
OL,18,Fannual defence budget: the Army, the
OL,19,FNavy, the RAF, the nuclear deterrent,
OL,20,Fcyber - everything.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
