PN,31006
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774436770
OL,3,CTaxpayer support: The cavalry is
OL,4,Ccoming but not for everyone
OL,6,F"This could be a shock that's perhaps
OL,7,Fa third of the size of the previous
OL,8,Fone. Petrol prices and the energy
OL,9,Fprice cap will rise, but not to the
OL,10,Flevels we saw in 2022 and 2023."
OL,12,FIn September 2022, when energy prices
OL,13,Flast surged, Liz Truss responded with
OL,14,Fblanket support - subsidising bills
OL,15,Ffor every household in the UK.
OL,17,FThe average annual gas and electricity
OL,18,Fbill peaked at more than #4,200 after
OL,19,FRussia's invasion. The government
OL,20,Fcapped bills at #2,500 and paid the
OL,21,Fdifference.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
